text='''[Note]:''' this page refers to the core pmwiki, as distributed from [[http://www.pmwiki.org|this site]]. Specific [[Skins:Skins|skins]] and [[Cookbook:Cookbook|add-ons]] may have different requirements, which they may have listed on their individual pages.%0a%0aPmWiki generates web pages (though generating pdf files and other formats is also [[Cookbook:Cookbook|possible]]). So in order to see its results, one needs a [[#browser|web browser]]. To make it serve those pages, PmWiki runs on top of an operating system (OS), under a web [[#server|web server]], and using the [[#php|php]] scripting language. The lists below address all these elements.%0a%0a[[#browser]]Here's a list of (browser, OS) combinations pmwiki output was tested with:%0a* [[http://mozilla.org | Firefox]]%0a* [[http://mozilla.org | Mozilla 1.7.6]],  Windows XP SP2  (mailto:jgreen@NOSPAM_mykmg.net)%0a* [[http://www.opera.com | Opera]]/[[http://www.access.co.jp/english/ | NetFront]] on Sharp Zaurus (SL5500 and SLC860), using embedded Apache 1.x with PHP 3.x%0a* PHP Version 5.0.4 + Mac OS X version 10.3.9 + FireFox v 1.03 %0a* [[http://www.apple.com/safari| Safari]], Mac OS X 10.3.x %0a%0a[[#server]]Here's a list of (web server, OS) combinations pmwiki was tested with:%0a* IIS 5.0, Windows 2000 SP4  (mailto:jgreen@NOSPAM_mykmg.net)%0a* IIS 5.1, Windows XP SP2 [[~newmy]]%0a* [[(http://www.)SAMBAR(.com)]] 6.2, Windows 2000 SP4 [[~newmy]]%0a* Apache/1.3.28, SUSE Linux 9.0 [[~newmy]]%0a%0agunde%0a%0a[[#php]]Here's a list of (php version, OS) combinations the develeoper and recipe writers use (earlier php versions could be used with partial loss of functionality):%0a* [[http://www.php.net/downloads.php#v4 | PHP 4.3.11]], Windows 2000 SP4  (mailto:jgreen@NOSPAM_mykmg.net)%0a* [[http://www.php.net/downloads.php#v4 | PHP 4.3.3]], Windows 2000 SP4  [[~newmy]]%0a* [[http://www.php.net/downloads.php#v5 | PHP 5.0.3]], Windows XP SP2  [[~newmy]]%0a* [[http://www.php.net/downloads.php#v4 | PHP 4.3.3]], SUSE Linux 9.0 [[~newmy]]%0a%0aQ: When installing PHP for PmWiki on IIS do you recommend IIS ISAPI or IIS CGI?%0aA: Use IIS ISAPI%0a%0a
